This paper is primarily focused on image synthesis and detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for detecting fake faces, which involves monitoring neuron behavior, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses potential security threats, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses public high-resolution face datasets, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
